    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Custom pairs and gutter</h2>
      <p><code>--space-s-l</code> is a custom pair skipping two steps, useful for larger layout jumps. <code>--gutter</code> is a global fluid token used in components like banners and wrappers. Each layout composition has its own namespaced gap token (e.g. <code>--cluster-gutter</code>, <code>--grid-gutter</code>) — override those at the composition level to adjust spacing independently.</p>

    
      <div class="">
  <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem 0;">
    <div class="cluster gap">
      <div style="width: var(--gutter); height: 1rem; background: var(--color-status-ok, #1a4); border-radius: 0.125rem;"></div>
      <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-xs);">
        <span ><code>--gutter</code></span>
        <span class="text-s color-neutral-600">clamp(1rem, calc(0.7rem + 1.52vw), 1.88rem)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cluster gap">
      <div style="width: var(--space-s-l); height: 1rem; background: var(--color-status-ok, #1a4); border-radius: 0.125rem;"></div>
      <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-xs);">
        <span ><code>--space-s-l</code></span>
        <span class="text-s color-neutral-600">clamp(1rem, calc(0.48rem + 2.61vw), 2.5rem)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
