        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div style=&quot;display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem 0;&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;cluster gap-s&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div style=&quot;flex-shrink: 0;&quot; style=&quot;width: var(--gutter); height: 1rem; background: var(--color-status-ok, #1a4); border-radius: 0.125rem;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;flow&quot; style=&quot;--flow-space: var(--space-xs);&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span &gt;&lt;code&gt;--gutter&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;text-s color-neutral-600&quot;&gt;clamp(1rem, calc(0.7rem + 1.52vw), 1.88rem)&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;cluster gap-s&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div style=&quot;flex-shrink: 0;&quot; style=&quot;width: var(--space-s-l); height: 1rem; background: var(--color-status-ok, #1a4); border-radius: 0.125rem;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;flow&quot; style=&quot;--flow-space: var(--space-xs);&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span &gt;&lt;code&gt;--space-s-l&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;text-s color-neutral-600&quot;&gt;clamp(1rem, calc(0.48rem + 2.61vw), 2.5rem)&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>

      <h3>Using composition gap tokens</h3>
      <p>Each layout composition exposes its own namespaced gap token. Override it locally on the element to adjust spacing for a specific section without affecting the global scale:</p>
      <pre><code>&lt;!-- Default cluster gap --&gt;
  &lt;div class="cluster"&gt;
    &lt;a href="/home/"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a href="/products/"&gt;Products&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- Tight gap for a compact toolbar --&gt;
  &lt;div class="cluster" style="--cluster-gutter: var(--space-xs)"&gt;
    &lt;button&gt;Bold&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button&gt;Italic&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button&gt;Underline&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- Override grid gap --&gt;
  &lt;div class="grid" style="--grid-gutter: var(--space-s)"&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;…&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Legacy unit <code>--su</code></h2>
      <p><code>--su</code> is a BBC GEL-derived spacing unit equal to <code>0.5rem</code> (~8px). It was used in the original utility classes (<code>.padding-*</code>, <code>.margin-*</code>) and is retained for backward compatibility. New component work should use the <code>--space-*</code> token scale instead.</p>
      <div class="callout wide" data-variant="brand" role="note"><p><code>--su</code> is appropriate when hard 8 px-grid alignment is required — for example, icon gutters or toolbar gaps that must align to a pixel grid. In all other cases prefer the fluid <code>--space-*</code> scale.</p></div>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Token table</h2>

      <table class="">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Token</th><th>Default (clamp)</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--su</code></td><td><code>0.5rem</code></td><td>Legacy BBC GEL 8 px unit — kept for compat</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--gutter</code></td><td><code>clamp(1rem, calc(0.7rem + 1.52vw), 1.88rem)</code></td><td>Global fluid inline gutter — used by wrappers and banners</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-tiny</code></td><td><code>clamp(0.25rem, calc(0.23rem + 0.11vw), 0.31rem)</code></td><td>~4 px — icon nudges, hairline gaps</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-xxs</code></td><td><code>clamp(0.5rem, calc(0.46rem + 0.22vw), 0.63rem)</code></td><td>~8 px — tight component padding</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-xs</code></td><td><code>clamp(0.75rem, calc(0.68rem + 0.33vw), 0.94rem)</code></td><td>~12 px — button padding, small gaps</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-s</code></td><td><code>clamp(1rem, calc(0.91rem + 0.43vw), 1.25rem)</code></td><td>~16 px — standard component padding</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-m</code></td><td><code>clamp(1.5rem, calc(1.37rem + 0.65vw), 1.88rem)</code></td><td>~24 px — card padding, list gaps</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-l</code></td><td><code>clamp(2rem, calc(1.83rem + 0.87vw), 2.5rem)</code></td><td>~32 px — section internal spacing</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-xl</code></td><td><code>clamp(3rem, calc(2.74rem + 1.3vw), 3.75rem)</code></td><td>~48 px — between-section gaps</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-xxl</code></td><td><code>clamp(4rem, calc(3.65rem + 1.74vw), 5rem)</code></td><td>~64 px — page-level regions</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-huge</code></td><td><code>clamp(6rem, calc(5.48rem + 2.61vw), 7.5rem)</code></td><td>~96 px — hero sections, large blocks</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-tiny-xxs</code></td><td><code>clamp(0.25rem, calc(0.12rem + 0.65vw), 0.63rem)</code></td><td>One-up pair: tiny → xxs</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-xxs-xs</code></td><td><code>clamp(0.5rem, calc(0.35rem + 0.76vw), 0.94rem)</code></td><td>One-up pair: xxs → xs</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-xs-s</code></td><td><code>clamp(0.75rem, calc(0.58rem + 0.87vw), 1.25rem)</code></td><td>One-up pair: xs → s</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-s-m</code></td><td><code>clamp(1rem, calc(0.7rem + 1.52vw), 1.88rem)</code></td><td>One-up pair: s → m</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-m-l</code></td><td><code>clamp(1.5rem, calc(1.15rem + 1.74vw), 2.5rem)</code></td><td>One-up pair: m → l</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-l-xl</code></td><td><code>clamp(2rem, calc(1.39rem + 3.04vw), 3.75rem)</code></td><td>One-up pair: l → xl</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-xl-xxl</code></td><td><code>clamp(3rem, calc(2.3rem + 3.48vw), 5rem)</code></td><td>One-up pair: xl → xxl</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-xxl-huge</code></td><td><code>clamp(4rem, calc(2.78rem + 6.09vw), 7.5rem)</code></td><td>One-up pair: xxl → huge</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--space-s-l</code></td><td><code>clamp(1rem, calc(0.48rem + 2.61vw), 2.5rem)</code></td><td>Custom pair skipping s → l</td></tr>
